## 7. Post-Incident Review

After every SEV-1 or SEV-2 incident, complete this review within 48 hours of resolution. File the completed review in `docs/incidents/YYYY-MM-DD-[brief-slug].md`.

- **Date:** [YYYY-MM-DD of the incident]
- **Severity:** [SEV-1 / SEV-2]
- **Timeline:**
  - Detected: [time and how it was detected]
  - Contained: [time and what containment action was taken]
  - Resolved: [time and what constituted resolution]
- **Root Cause:** [What caused the incident — be specific. "Human error" is not sufficient; describe the exact action and the system property that made it possible.]
- **Impact:** [What was affected — number of users, data records involved, duration of unavailability, any data loss or corruption.]
- **Resolution:** [What was done to fix it — specific actions, commands run, rollback performed, secrets rotated, etc.]
- **Preventive Measures:** [What changed as a result — code changes, process changes, monitoring additions, documentation updates. Include links to PRs or commits where applicable.]

